               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Gadla Qirqos “Vita of Cyricus” (fols. 3ra-98vb) 
 II) Taʾammǝra
                     Qirqos “Miracles of Cyricus” (fols. 99ra-130rb): 33 miracles.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <locus from="3ra" to="130rb"/>
                     <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5739GadlaQDossier">Hagiographic Dossier of Sts Cyricus and Julitta</title>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                        <locus from="3ra" to="98vb"/>
                        <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1488GadlaQ">Gadla Qirqos</title>
                        <note>- Text I is divided into sections to be read each month, the same as
                           in<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESamq007">AMQ-007</ref>.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2">
                        <locus from="99ra" to="130rb"/>
                        <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT4669TaammeraQi">Taʾammǝra Qirqos</title>
                        <note>- In Text II, all the 33 miracles are numbered. The numeral 27 is repeted
                           twice and the following numeration continues wrongly, so that the last
                           numeral is 32 instead of 33.</note>
                        <note>The miracles are the same and in the same sequence as<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESamq007">AMQ-007</ref>.</note>
                     </msItem>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  
                  
